Creating Map Visual 14

Creating Map for Violation Per Month in each US State

Steps

Violation Per Month in each State

  1.        Open Visualization Pane
  2.        Select   Map Visualization
  3.        Drag the visual on to the dashboard
  4.        Drag State field from Traffic Violation table to Location ,Violation Per Month to Color Saturation , Total Violation, %Out of State and YOY to Tooltips

                                       

       

     Violation Per Month in each State Map Formatting

  1.        General: X - Position = 716, Y - Position =85, Width = 564, Height = 298
  2.        Data Color : Diverging ON: Minimum = #7A907C,  Center = #E8D166 , Maximum = #F5C4AF
  3.       Shape: MAP - USA States and Projection : Albers USA  
  4.        Default Color : #005C2E
  5.        Title ON ,   Text Title = "Violation Per Month by State", Font Color = #FFFFFF , Background Color = #073501 , Font Size = 14 and Font Family = DIN
  6.        Border ON, Color = #E6E6E6 , Radius = 0



            

Use only US Maps

Some insights for how we can create different type maps visuals in Power BI Desktop
